  "source_notes": "Marion March quotes birth certificate.  ''CAO Times'' states that the time (normally CST) was set to EST for business reasons. \\nNo confirmation could be found for this claim. Plain is in the western part of the state, in Sumter county's western part. The CST/EST boundary goes across Sumter county, and Plains was clearly in the CST section. It followed [https://www.appenmedia.com/opinion/opinion-when-georgia-had-two-time-zones/article_0bb3e6c4-9c84-11eb-a1f5-6b1a42a8e61a.html Central time] until 21 March 1941.\\n\\nIn June 2019 Sy Scholfield provided photo of birth record stating time of birth as \"seven A.M.\" The record is held at the Jimmy Carter Presidential Library and Museum and a photo of it was published online by Sage Scott [https://everydaywanderer.com/jimmy-carter-museum]. The Rodden Rating was thus upgraded to \"BC/BR in hand.\"\\n",
